'''動物試驗'''（{{lang-en|animal testing}}）、'''動物實驗'''（{{lang-en|animal experimentation}}）或'''动物研究'''（{{lang-en|animal research}}），是指利用[[人類|人類]]以外的動物進行[[科學實驗|科學實驗]]，以驗證個別因素對接受測試的動物在[[生理|生理]]或[[行為|行為]]上的影響，並與同種類之生物在[[自然環境|自然環境]]下的狀態進行比對。用于动物实验的动物称为“实验动物”（{{Lang-en|laboratory animals}}）。其目的是为了[[生理学|生理学]]、[[病理学|病理学]]或[[心理学|心理学]]的研究<ref name="selectcommintro">{{Cite web |title="Introduction", Select Committee on Animals In Scientific Procedures Report |url=http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200102/ldselect/ldanimal/150/15004.htm#a7 |accessdate=2012-07-13 |publisher=UK Parliament |language=en |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120908112006/http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200102/ldselect/ldanimal/150/15004.htm%23a7#a7 |archivedate=2012-09-08 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。动物的实验研究通常在综合大学、医学院、制药公司、国防机构以及为各行各业提供动物测试服务的商业设施中进行<ref name=selectcommintro/>。动物试验的重点在于纯粹研究的连续性，侧重于发展有机体的基础知识、应用研究，也可能侧重于回答一些具有重大实际意义的问题，例如寻找治愈疾病的方法。这项研究应用的具体例子包括测试疾病的治疗方法、选育、国防研究和{{le|毒理学测试|Toxicology testing|毒理学}}，甚至还包括化妆品测试。{{FACT|在教育领域，动物试验有时也是生物学或者心理学课程的一部分。这些实践操作在不同国家受到不同程度的监管。|time=2019-08-25}}

据估计，脊椎动物在动物试验中每年的使用量——从[[斑马鱼|斑马鱼]]到非人类[[灵长类动物|灵长类动物]]——其范围从数亿到十数亿<ref>{{Cite web |title=Alternatives to animal testing gaining ground |url=https://www.baltimoresun.com/health/bs-xpm-2010-08-26-bs-hs-animal-testing-20100826-story.html |accessdate=2019-08-02 |date=2010-08-26 |last=Cohn |first=Meredith |work=baltimoresun.com |agency=The Baltimore Sun |language=en-US |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20120707075236/http://articles.baltimoresun.com/2010-08-26/health/bs-hs-animal-testing-20100826_1_animal-testing-animal-welfare-act-researchers |archivedate=2012-07-07 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。{{FACT|在欧盟，脊椎动物物种占研究中使用动物的93％，2011年使用了1150万只动物。|time=2019-08-25}}据估计，2001年仅在美国使用的小鼠和大鼠的数量为8000万只<ref name="Carbone26">Carbone 2004, p. 26.</ref>。小鼠、大鼠、鱼类、两栖动物和爬行动物总共占研究使用动物总数的85％以上<ref name="EUstatistics2013">{{cite web|title=EU statistics show decline in animal research numbers|url=http://speakingofresearch.com/2013/12/12/eu-statistics-show-decline-in-animal-research-numbers/|publisher=Speaking of Research|year=2013|accessdate=2016-01-24|archive-date=2017-10-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171006162448/https://speakingofresearch.com/2013/12/12/eu-statistics-show-decline-in-animal-research-numbers/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

大多数动物在实验结束后会被[[安乐死|安乐死]]<ref name="Carbone22">Carbone 2004, p, 22</ref>。{{le|实验室动物来源|Laboratory animal sources|实验动物的来源}}因国家和物种而异；大多数实验用动物都来源于人工目的性培育，少数是在野外捕获或者由通过拍卖和[[动物收容所|动物收容所]]获得的经销商提供<ref>"Use of Laboratory Animals in Biomedical and Behavioral Research", Institute for Laboratory Animal Research, The National Academies Press, 1988 {{ISBN|0-309-07878-4}}.</ref><ref>Cooper, Sylvia (1 August 1999). [http://chronicle.augusta.com/stories/1999/08/01/met_266886.shtml "Pets crowd animal shelter"] {{Wayback|url=http://chronicle.augusta.com/stories/1999/08/01/met_266886.shtml |date=20140202203913 }}, ''The Augusta Chronicle''.</ref><ref name=Gillham>{{Cite web |title=Inside the Horrible Trade in Dogs for Reseach |url=https://www.newsweek.com/inside-horrible-trade-dogs-reseach-113635 |accessdate=2019-08-02 |date=2006-02-16 |last=Christina |first=Gillham |work=Newsweek |language=en |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190802155013/https://www.newsweek.com/inside-horrible-trade-dogs-reseach-113635 |archivedate=2019-08-02 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[英国皇家学会|英国皇家学会]]等动物实验支持者认为，实际上20世纪的每一项医学成就都依赖于某种方式的动物使用<ref name="TheRoyalSociety">[http://royalsociety.org/The-use-of-non-human-animals-in-research-a-guide-for-scientists/ The use of non-human animals in research: a guide for scientists] [[The_Royal_Society|The Royal Society]], 2004, p. 1</ref>。[[美国国家科学院|美国国家科学院]]实验动物研究所认为，即使是复杂的计算机模型也无法取代动物研究，这些模型无法处理分子、细胞、组织、器官、生物体以及环境之间极其复杂的相互作用<ref>[http://books.nap.edu/openbook.php?record_id=10733 "Science, Medicine, and Animals"] {{Wayback|url=http://books.nap.edu/openbook.php?record_id=10733 |date=20141016144712 }}, Institute for Laboratory Animal Research, Published by the [[United_States_National_Academy_of_Sciences|National Research Council of the National Academies]] 2004, p. 2</ref>。[[动物权利|动物权利]]组织，如[[善待动物组织|PETA]]和[[英国废除活体解剖联盟|BUAV]]质疑动物试验的必要性和合法性，认为这些试验[[虐待動物|残忍]]且缺乏有效管理，并认为由于误导性的动物模型无法可靠地预测人类的影响，一些试验已经过时，成本超过了益处，另一方面也认为动物具有在实验中不被使用或受到伤害的内在权利<ref name="croce" /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.peta.org/about/faq-viv.asp |title=About |work=Peta.org |date= |accessdate=2015-04-06 |archive-date=2010-06-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100625223019/http://www.peta.org/about/faq-viv.asp |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.buav.org/pdf/UK-Legislation.pdf |title=UK Legislation: A Criticism |work=Web.archive.org |accessdate=2015-04-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080625161126/http://www.buav.org/pdf/UK-Legislation.pdf |archivedate=2008-06-25 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.buav.org/pdf/VivisectionFAQs.pdf |title=FAQs: Vivisection |publisher=[[British_Union_for_the_Abolition_of_Vivisection|British Union for the Abolition of Vivisection]] |accessdate=2015-04-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150513021651/http://www.buav.org/pdf/VivisectionFAQs.pdf |archivedate=2015-05-13 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.humanesociety.org/issues/biomedical_research/ |title=Biomedical Research : The Humane Society of the United States |work=Humanesociety.org |date= |accessdate=2015-04-06 |archive-date=2020-09-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200930150512/https://www.humanesociety.org/all-our-fights/taking-suffering-out-science |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pcrm.org/resch/anexp/index.html |title=Animal Testing and Animal Experimentation Issues | Physicians Committee |work=Pcrm.org |date= |accessdate=2015-04-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723001342/http://www.pcrm.org/resch/anexp/index.html |archivedate=2011-07-23 |df= }}</ref>。

==定义==
术语“动物试验”、“动物实验”、“动物研究”、“[[in_vivo|活体]]实验”以及“活体解剖”具有相似的表征但内涵各异。从字面上看，“活体解剖”是指动物的“活体剖切”，并且历史上仅涉及[[解剖|解剖]]活体动物的实验。该术语偶尔用于贬损任何使用活体动物的实验；例如《[[大英百科全书|大英百科全书]]》将“活体解剖”定义为：“对活体动物进行实验而非治疗目的的操作，更广泛的说法还包含所有对活体动物所进行的实验”<ref name=croce>{{Cite book |url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/40964944 |title=Vivisection or science? : an investigation into testing drugs and safeguarding health |last=Croce |first=Pietro |date=1999 |publisher=Zed Books in association with Doctors and Lawyers for Responsible Medicine |isbn=1856497321 |edition=更新修订版 |location=London |oclc=40964944 |access-date=2019-08-03 |archive-date=2008-09-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080928230729/http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/40964944 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title="Vivisection" |url=http://www.britannica.com/ebc/article-9382118?query=Vivisection&ct= |date=2007 |work=Encyclopædia Britannica |language=en |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080101153454/http://www.britannica.com/ebc/article-9382118?query=Vivisection&ct= |archivedate=2008-01-01 |accessdate=2019-08-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=buavfaq>{{cite web |url=http://www.buav.org/pdf/VivisectionFAQs.pdf |title=Vivisection FAQ |publisher=British Union for the Abolition of Vivisection |format=pdf |deadurl=yes |language=en |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150513021651/http://www.buav.org/pdf/VivisectionFAQs.pdf |archivedate=2015-05-13 |accessdate=2019-08-02 }}</ref>然而词典指出这层更宽泛的定义是“仅由反对此类工作的人所使用”<ref>定义引用自：
*{{Cite web |title=Vivisection <nowiki>|</nowiki> Encyclopedia.com |url=https://www.encyclopedia.com/medicine/divisions-diagnostics-and-procedures/medicine/vivisection#vivisection |accessdate=2019-08-03 |work=www.encyclopedia.com |language=en |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190803015947/https://www.encyclopedia.com/medicine/divisions-diagnostics-and-procedures/medicine/vivisection%23vivisection#vivisection |archivedate=2019-08-03 |dead-url=no }}
*{{Cite web |title=Definition of VIVISECTION |url=https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/vivisection |accessdate=2019-08-03 |work=www.merriam-webster.com |language=en |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130128114059/http://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/vivisection |archivedate=2013-01-28 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。这个词具有负面含义，意味着折磨，痛苦和死亡<ref name=Carbone22/>。因此“活体解剖”这个词对于那些反对这一系列研究的人来说是首选，而科学家们则通常使用“动物实验”一词<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Paixão RL, Schramm FR | title = Ethics and animal experimentation: what is debated? | journal = Cadernos de Saúde Pública | volume = 15 | issue = Suppl 1 | pages = 99–110 | year = 1999 | pmid = 10089552 | doi=10.1590/s0102-311x1999000500011 }}</ref><ref>Yarri, Donna (2005). ''The Ethics of Animal Experimentation'', Oxford University Press U.S., {{ISBN|0-19-518179-4}}.</ref>。
==历史==
<!--{{Main|动物试验的历史}}-->
[[Image:An_Experiment_on_a_Bird_in_an_Air_Pump_by_Joseph_Wright_of_Derby,_1768.jpg|thumb]]》是{{tsl|en|Joseph Wright of Derby|德比的约瑟夫·赖特}}1768年的[[油画|布面油画]]作品]]

动物试验的最早参考文献见于公元前2世纪和4世纪的希腊书籍。[[亚里士多德|亚里士多德]]和[[埃拉西斯特拉图斯|埃拉西斯特拉图斯]]被认为是最早进行活体动物实验的人<ref>Cohen and Loew 1984.</ref>。2世纪的罗马医生[[盖伦|盖伦]]首次解剖了猪和山羊，因此他也被称为“活体解剖之父”<ref name=lpag>{{cite web |url=http://www.lpag.org/layperson/layperson.html#history |title=History of nonhuman animal research |publisher=Laboratory Primate Advocacy Group |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20061013110949/http://www.lpag.org/layperson/layperson.html#history |archivedate=2006-10-13 |accessdate=2018-09-03 }}</ref>。12世纪[[安达卢斯|安达卢斯]]的[[中世纪伊斯兰世界的医学|阿拉伯医生]][[伊本·苏尔|伊本·苏尔]]也进行了动物解剖；他首次将动物试验作为一种测试外科手术程序的实验方法，并将其测试结果应用到人类患者身上<ref name=Rabie2005>{{cite journal | author = Abdel-Halim RE | title = Contributions of Ibn Zuhr (Avenzoar) to the progress of surgery: a study and translations from his book Al-Taisir | journal = Saudi Medical Journal | volume = 26 | issue = 9 | pages = 1333–9 | year = 2005 | pmid = 16155644 }}</ref><ref name=Rabie2006>{{cite journal | author = Abdel-Halim RE | title = Contributions of Muhadhdhab Al-Deen Al-Baghdadi to the progress of medicine and urology. A study and translations from his book Al-Mukhtar | journal = Saudi Medical Journal | volume = 27 | issue = 11 | pages = 1631–41 | year = 2006 | pmid = 17106533 }}</ref>。

在生物医学历史中，动物被反复地使用。1831年，[[都柏林动物园|都柏林动物园]]的创始人们开始着眼于研究活着的或者已经死亡了的动物<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.independent.ie/lifestyle/the-great-zoos-who-2669960.html | work=Irish Independent | first=John | last=Costello | title=The great zoo's who | date=2011-06-09 | accessdate=2019-08-03 | archive-date=2013-01-16 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130116232229/http://www.independent.ie/lifestyle/the-great-zoos-who-2669960.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。在19世纪80年代，[[路易·巴斯德|路易·巴斯德]]通过在绵羊身上引发[[炭疽病|炭疽病]]，令人信服地证明了疾病的{{le|病菌學說|Germ theory of disease|细菌理论}}<ref>{{Cite web |title=你的扁桃腺還在嗎？──《科倫醫生吐真言：醫學爭議教我們的二三事》 |url=https://pansci.asia/archives/97008 |accessdate=2019-08-03 |date=2016-04-24 |work=PanSci 泛科學 |language=zh-TW |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190803031258/https://pansci.asia/archives/97008 |archivedate=2019-08-03 |quote=這種觀念是一八七○年代病菌學說（the germ theory of disease）帶來 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="pmid11544370">{{cite journal | vauthors = Mock M, Fouet A | title = Anthrax | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_annual-review-of-microbiology_2001_55/page/647 | journal = Annu. Rev. Microbiol. | volume = 55 | pages = 647–71 | year = 2001 | pmid = 11544370 | doi = 10.1146/annurev.micro.55.1.647 }}</ref>。于此同期的[[罗伯特·科赫|罗伯特·科赫]]则使老鼠和豚鼠感染了炭疽病和[[结核病|结核病]]。在19世纪90年代，[[伊万·巴甫洛夫|伊万·巴甫洛夫]]使用狗来描述“[[条件反射|条件反射]]”则可能是最著名的动物试验实例<ref name="pmid3309839">{{cite journal | author = Windholz G | title = Pavlov as a psychologist. A reappraisal | journal = Pavlovian J. Biol. Sci. | volume = 22 | issue = 3 | pages = 103–12 | year = 1987 | pmid = 3309839 }}</ref>。{{FACT|在第一次世界大战中，德国特工使进入俄国的绵羊都携带了炭疽病毒，并为法国骑兵的骡子和马接种了马鼻疽病以期达到战略目的。|time=2019-08-25}}1917年至1918年间，德军使投往美军阵地的骡子染上病菌，病最终造成200头骡子死亡<ref name="maczulak">{{citation | author=Anne Maczulak | entry=bioweapon | encyclopedia =Encyclopedia of Microbiology | year=2011 | publisher=Facts On File | pages=127–135 | isbn=978-0-8160-7364-1}}</ref>。[[胰岛素|胰岛素]]于1922年首次从狗身上分离出来，彻底改变了[[糖尿病|糖尿病]]的治疗方法<ref name="pmid9285027">{{cite journal | author = Gorden P | title = Non-insulin dependent diabetes—the past, present and future | journal = Ann. Acad. Med. Singap. | volume = 26 | issue = 3 | pages = 326–30 | year = 1997 | pmid = 9285027 }}</ref>。1957年11月3日，一条[[蘇聯太空犬|蘇聯太空犬]][[萊卡_(犬)|萊卡]]成为第一支只在{{le|动物在太空中|Animals in space|绕地球轨道运行的动物}}。在20世纪70年代，医学界研究者使用[[犰狳|犰狳]]来研发抗生素疗法和麻风病疫苗<ref name="pmid7242665">{{cite journal | author = Walgate R | title = Armadillos fight leprosy | journal = Nature | volume = 291 | issue = 5816 | page = 527 | year = 1981 | pmid = 7242665 | doi = 10.1038/291527a0 | bibcode = 1981Natur.291..527W }}</ref>，之后再运用在人类身上<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Scollard DM, Adams LB, Gillis TP, Krahenbuhl JL, Truman RW, Williams DL | title = The Continuing Challenges of Leprosy | journal = Clin. Microbiol. Rev. | volume = 19 | issue = 2 | pages = 338–81 | year = 2006 | pmid = 16614253 | pmc = 1471987 | doi = 10.1128/CMR.19.2.338-381.2006 }}</ref>。人类改变动物[[遗传学|遗传学]]的能力在1974年向前迈出了一大步，当时[[鲁道夫·耶尼施|鲁道夫·耶尼施]]已经能够通过将来自[[SV40|SV40]]病毒的DNA整合到小鼠[[基因组|基因组]]中从而成功的生产出第一种[[转基因生物|转基因哺乳动物]]<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Jaenisch R, Mintz B | title = Simian Virus 40 DNA Sequences in DNA of Healthy Adult Mice Derived from Preimplantation Blastocysts Injected with Viral DNA | journal = Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America | volume = 71 | issue = 4 | pages = 1250–4 | year = 1974 | pmid = 4364530 | pmc = 388203 | doi = 10.1073/pnas.71.4.1250 | bibcode = 1974PNAS...71.1250J }}</ref>。这项基因研究的进展十分迅速，到了1996年成功诞生的[[多莉|绵羊多利]]是第一个从成年供体细胞中[[分子選殖|克隆]]出来的哺乳动物<ref name=Wilmut/><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.understandinganimalresearch.org.uk/resources/animal-research-essay-resources/history-of-animal-research/|title=History of animal research|website=www.understandinganimalresearch.org.uk|access-date=2016-04-08|archive-date=2018-10-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181007051114/http://www.understandinganimalresearch.org.uk/resources/animal-research-essay-resources/history-of-animal-research|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

{{FACT|在19世纪的时候，各国管制药物的法律都较为宽松。例如在美国，当时的政府只能在一家公司因销售损害顾客的产品而被起诉之后才能禁用其生产的药品。|time=2019-08-25}}而到了20世纪，药物毒理学试验变得日趋重要。1937年爆发的{{le|磺胺酏剂|Elixir sulfanilamide}}灾难最终杀死了100多名使用者。为此美国国会通过法律要求在药物上市之前先在动物身上进行安全测试。在这之后其他国家也纷纷颁布了类似的法律<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fda.gov/AboutFDA/WhatWeDo/History/ProductRegulation/SulfanilamideDisaster/default.htm |title=Taste of Raspberries, Taste of Death. The 1937 Elixir Sulfanilamide Incident |work=FDA Consumer magazine |date=June 1981 |accessdate=2019-08-03 |archive-date=2017-07-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170722143400/https://www.fda.gov/AboutFDA/WhatWeDo/History/ProductRegulation/SulfanilamideDisaster/default.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在20世纪60年代，由于发生了[[沙利度胺|沙利度胺]]悲剧，各国政府又进一步完善了法律条文，要求在药物出售之前，必须针对孕妇的反应进行安全性测试<ref name =Burkholz>{{Cite news | first =Herbert | last =Burkholz | title =Giving Thalidomide a Second Chance | url =http://www.fda.gov/fdac/features/1997/697_thal.html | work =FDA Consumer | publisher =US [[Food_and_Drug_Administration|Food and Drug Administration]] | date =1997-09-01 | accessdate =2019-08-03 | archive-date =2009-05-13 | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20090513023028/http://www.fda.gov/fdac/features/1997/697_thal.html | dead-url =no }}</ref>。

==历史争议==
[[Image:Claude_Bernard_5.jpg|left]]<ref name=Croce11/>认为动物实验“对于人类毒理学和卫生学是完全有说服力的”<ref name=Bernard>[[Claude_Bernard|Bernard, Claude]] ''An Introduction to the Study of Experimental Medicine'', 1865. First English translation by Henry Copley Greene, published by Macmillan & Co., Ltd., 1927; reprinted in 1949, p. 125.</ref>]]
随着动物实验量尤其是活体解剖实践的上升，批评和争议也随之增加。1655年，“盖伦生理学”的倡导者{{le|埃德蒙·奥马拉|Edmund O'Meara}}{{#tag:ref|译名参考自《世界人名翻译大辞典》。{{Sfn|新华社译名室|1993|p=842,2052}}|group="注释"}}说：“活体解剖的悲惨折磨体现在使躯体处于不自然的状态”<ref name=Ryder54>[[Richard_D._Ryder|Ryder, Richard D.]] (2000). ''Animal Revolution: Changing Attitudes Towards Speciesism''. Berg Publishers, p. 54 {{ISBN|1-85973-330-1}}.</ref><ref name=ANZCCART>[https://web.archive.org/web/20090327033757/http://www.adelaide.edu.au/ANZCCART/resources/AnimalExperimentation.pdf "Animal Experimentation: A Student Guide to Balancing the Issues"], Australian and New Zealand Council for the Care of Animals in Research and Teaching (ANZCCART), accessed 12 December 2007, cites original reference in Maehle, A-H. and Tr6hler, U. ''Animal experimentation from antiquity to the end of the eighteenth century: attitudes and arguments''. In N. A. Rupke (ed.) Vivisection in Historical Perspective. Croom Helm, London, 1987, p. 22.</ref>。奥马拉也和其他研究者一样认为动物生理学可能会受到活体解剖过程中疼痛的影响，使得结果变得不可靠。而另一方面，在[[伦理学|道德]]的基础上也存在异议，越来越多的人认为“对人类有益并不能说明对动物的伤害是正当的行为”。许多人也认为动物并不同于人类，因此在动物的结果并不能应用于人类<ref name=ANZCCART/>。

而争议的另一端，赞成动物试验的人认为动物实验对于推进医学和生物学知识是十分必要的。被称为“活体解剖王子”和“生理学之父”的克洛德·贝尔纳<ref name=Croce11>Croce, Pietro. ''Vivisection or Science? An Investigation into Testing Drugs and Safeguarding Health''. Zed Books, 1999, {{ISBN|1-85649-732-1}} p. 11.</ref>和他的妻子玛丽·弗朗索瓦·马丁（Marie Françoise Martin）于1883年在法国创立了第一个反活体解剖学会<ref>Rudacille, Deborah (2000). ''The Scalpel and the Butterfly: The Conflict'', University of California Press, p. 19 {{ISBN|0-520-23154-6}}.</ref>，并在1865年写道“生命科学是一个极好的，令人眼花缭乱的大厅，只有通过一个漫长而可怕的厨房才能到达”<ref name=TelegraphNov2003>[https://web.archive.org/web/20080213180427/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/health/main.jhtml?xml=%2Fhealth%2F2003%2F11%2F24%2Fhsick23.xml "In sickness and in health: vivisection's undoing"], ''The Daily Telegraph'', November 2003</ref>。并认为“动物实验……对于人类的毒理学和卫生学来说是完全具有说服力的……除了程度，其对人类和动物的影响是相同的”<ref name=Bernard/>。贝尔纳最终将动物试验确立为标准[[科学方法|科学方法]]的一部分<ref name=LaFollette>LaFollette, H., Shanks, N., [http://www.hughlafollette.com/papers/BERNARD.HTM Animal Experimentation: the Legacy of Claude Bernard] {{Wayback|url=http://www.hughlafollette.com/papers/BERNARD.HTM |date=20180609192221 }}, ''International Studies in the Philosophy of Science'' (1994) pp. 195–210.</ref>。

1896年，生理学家兼医生{{le|沃尔特·布拉德福德·坎农|Walter Bradford Cannon}}{{#tag:ref|译名参考自搜狐网。<ref>{{Cite web |title=一滴血都没流却失血过多而亡，这是真的吗？_手机搜狐网 |url=http://m.sohu.com/a/297759578_119097 |accessdate=2019-08-03 |author=果壳网 |date=2019-02-26 |work=m.sohu.com |language=zh-cn |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190803081520/http://m.sohu.com/a/297759578_119097 |archivedate=2019-08-03 |quote=1942年，美国生理学家沃尔特·布拉德福德·坎农（Walter Bradford Cannon）发…… |dead-url=no }}</ref>|group="注释"}}博士说：“反活体解剖学家们是[[西奥多·罗斯福|西奥多·罗斯福]]两种类型人中的第二种，‘没有良心的常识可能会导致犯罪，但没有常识的良心可能会招致愚蠢 ，这是犯罪的帮凶。’”<ref>{{cite journal | author = Nicoll CS | title = A Physiologist's Views on the Animal Rights/Liberation Movement | journal = The Physiologist | volume = 34 | issue = 6 | pages = 303, 306–8, 315 | year = 1991 | pmid = 1775539 }}</ref>。在20世纪初的{{le|布朗狗事件|Brown Dog affair}}{{#tag:ref|另有来源译为“棕色獵犬暴動”。<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com.sg/books?id=_Ib5DQAAQBAJ&pg=PA63&lpg=PA63&dq=Brown+Dog+affair+%25E6%25A3%2595%25E8%2589%25B2%25E7%258D%25B5%25E7%258A%25AC%25E6%259A%25B4%25E5%258B%2595&source=bl&ots=H68YpxHNHz&sig=ACfU3U0SPjvyAlX2HDE6TjENUzWG81nQfQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiQ3rTJrObjAhW7H7kGHZmVBQoQ6AEwC3oECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=Brown%2520Dog%2520affair%2520%25E6%25A3%2595%25E8%2589%25B2%25E7%258D%25B5%25E7%258A%25AC%25E6%259A%25B4%25E5%258B%2595&f=false |title=胖病毒、人皮書、水蛭蒐集人: 醫療現場的46個震撼奇想 |last=蘇上豪 |date=2016-12-09 |publisher=時報文化出版 |isbn=9789571368450 |language=zh-TW |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190803090731/https://books.google.com.sg/books?id=_Ib5DQAAQBAJ&pg=PA63&lpg=PA63&dq=Brown+Dog+affair+%25E6%25A3%2595%25E8%2589%25B2%25E7%258D%25B5%25E7%258A%25AC%25E6%259A%25B4%25E5%258B%2595&source=bl&ots=H68YpxHNHz&sig=ACfU3U0SPjvyAlX2HDE6TjENUzWG81nQfQ&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiQ3rTJrObjAhW7H7kGHZmVBQoQ6AEwC3oECAkQAQ%23v=onepage&q=Brown%2520Dog%2520affair%2520%25E6%25A3%2595%25E8%2589%25B2%25E7%258D%25B5%25E7%258A%25AC%25E6%259A%25B4%25E5%258B%2595&f=false#v=onepage&q=Brown%2520Dog%2520affair%2520%25E6%25A3%2595%25E8%2589%25B2%25E7%258D%25B5%25E7%258A%25AC%25E6%259A%25B4%25E5%258B%2595&f=false |archivedate=2019-08-03 |quote=……史學家稱此事件為「棕色獵犬暴動」( Brown Dog Riot 或 Brown Dog Affair)…… |access-date=2019-08-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>|group="注释"}}中，亲动物和反动物试验团体之间的这些分歧首先引起了公众的注意，当时有数百名医学生和反活体解剖学家围绕着一尊为纪念被活体解剖的狗而立的纪念像与警察发生冲突<ref name=Mason>Mason, Peter. [http://www.london-books.co.uk/books/browndog.html ''The Brown Dog Affair''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.london-books.co.uk/books/browndog.html |date=20180520224543 }}. Two Sevens Publishing, 1997.</ref>。
[[Image:One_of_Pavlov's_dogs.jpg|thumb]]
1822年，英国议会颁布了第一部动物保护法，紧随其后的是1876年出台的《{{le|防止虐待动物法|Cruelty to Animals Act, 1876}}》{{#tag:ref|译名参考自《科技法学（第三版）》。<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com.sg/books?id=skhyDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT357&lpg=PT357&dq=%25E9%2598%25B2%25E6%25AD%25A2%25E6%25AE%258B%25E9%2585%25B7%25E5%25AF%25B9%25E5%25BE%2585%25E5%258A%25A8%25E7%2589%25A9%25E6%25B3%2595%25E6%25A1%2588%25E3%2580%258D%25EF%25BC%2588the+Cruelty+to+Animals+Act%25EF%25BC%2589&source=bl&ots=tNFIkyE8Pq&sig=ACfU3U036qz8gcn0QFr-xuKO8-CMvK0Frg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwje5KqDlOjjAhVMILkGHaOLA_AQ6AEwBHoECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=%25E9%2598%25B2%25E6%25AD%25A2%25E6%25AE%258B%25E9%2585%25B7%25E5%25AF%25B9%25E5%25BE%2585%25E5%258A%25A8%25E7%2589%25A9%25E6%25B3%2595%25E6%25A1%2588%25E3%2580%258D%25EF%25BC%2588the%2520Cruelty%2520to%2520Animals%2520Act%25EF%25BC%2589&f=false |title=科技法学（第三版） |last=何悦 |date=2016-10-01 |publisher=法律出版社 |isbn=9787519700058 |location=北京 |edition=第3版 |page=317 |language=zh |oclc=1099522095 |chapter=第十一章 实验动物福利法 第三节 部分国家实验动物福利法 |access-date=2019-08-04 |archive-date=2020-09-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200915053109/https://books.google.com.sg/books?id=skhyDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT357&lpg=PT357&dq=%25E9%2598%25B2%25E6%25AD%25A2%25E6%25AE%258B%25E9%2585%25B7%25E5%25AF%25B9%25E5%25BE%2585%25E5%258A%25A8%25E7%2589%25A9%25E6%25B3%2595%25E6%25A1%2588%25E3%2580%258D%25EF%25BC%2588the+Cruelty+to+Animals+Act%25EF%25BC%2589&source=bl&ots=tNFIkyE8Pq&sig=ACfU3U036qz8gcn0QFr-xuKO8-CMvK0Frg&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwje5KqDlOjjAhVMILkGHaOLA_AQ6AEwBHoECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=%25E9%2598%25B2%25E6%25AD%25A2%25E6%25AE%258B%25E9%2585%25B7%25E5%25AF%25B9%25E5%25BE%2585%25E5%258A%25A8%25E7%2589%25A9%25E6%25B3%2595%25E6%25A1%2588%25E3%2580%258D%25EF%25BC%2588the%2520Cruelty%2520to%2520Animals%2520Act%25EF%25BC%2589&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>|group="注释"}}，这是第一部专门针对动物试验的法律。查尔斯·达尔文于1871年3月写信给[[雷·兰克斯特|雷·兰克斯特]]{{#tag:ref|译名参考自《物種源起: 改變世界的經典--進化論》。<ref>{{Cite book |url=https://books.google.com.sg/books?id=M0d2CgAAQBAJ&pg=PT121&lpg=PT121&dq=Ray+Lankester+%25E9%259B%25B7&source=bl&ots=71nkm_xW8J&sig=ACfU3U137p0jaiLaz3RYYGfMfq7K6NJn7A&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiHi76Qm-jjAhXlH7kGHQUzBDAQ6AEwD3oECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=Ray%2520Lankester%2520%25E9%259B%25B7&f=false |title=物種源起: 改變世界的經典--進化論 |last=達爾文 |date=2015-08-31 |publisher=谷月社 |language=zh-TW |access-date=2019-08-04 |archive-date=2020-09-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200915054450/https://books.google.com.sg/books?id=M0d2CgAAQBAJ&pg=PT121&lpg=PT121&dq=Ray+Lankester+%25E9%259B%25B7&source=bl&ots=71nkm_xW8J&sig=ACfU3U137p0jaiLaz3RYYGfMfq7K6NJn7A&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwiHi76Qm-jjAhXlH7kGHQUzBDAQ6AEwD3oECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=Ray%2520Lankester%2520%25E9%259B%25B7&f=false |dead-url=no }}</ref>|group="注释"}}，提出了这项立法：“你问我对活体解剖的看法。对于生理学的真实研究是合理的；而不仅仅是因为该死的可恶的好奇心，对此我完全同意。”<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fullbooks.com/The-Life-and-Letters-of-Charles-Darwinx29407.html |title=''The Life and Letters of Charles Darwin, Volume II'' |publisher=Fullbooks.com |accessdate=2019-08-04 |archive-date=2018-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180927133953/http://www.fullbooks.com/The-Life-and-Letters-of-Charles-Darwinx29407.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>Bowlby, John (1991). ''Charles Darwin: A New Life'', W. W. Norton & Company, p. 420 {{ISBN|0-393-30930-4}}.</ref>为了应对反活体解剖学家的游说，英国成立了几个组织来保护动物研究：{{le|英国生理学会|The Physiological Society|生理学会}}成立于1876年，为生理学家提供“互惠互利和保护”<ref>{{cite book|last=Ilman|first=John|title=Animal Research in Medicine: 100 years of politics, protest and progress. The Story of the Research Defence Society|year=2008|publisher=Research Defence Society|isbn=978-0-9560008-0-4|page=16}}</ref> ；成立于1882年的研究促进医学协会专注于政策制定；而于1908年成立的{{le|研究防御学会|Research Defence Society}}（现为{{le|理解动物研究|Understanding Animal Research}}{{#tag:ref|译名参考自中国实验动物信息网。<ref>{{Cite web |title=欧盟放行灵长类动物研究 - 实验动物_中国实验动物信息网 |url=https://www.lascn.net/Item/1155.aspx |accessdate=2019-08-04 |date=2009-05-08 |work=www.lascn.net |language=zh-cn |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190804040541/https://www.lascn.net/Item/1155.aspx |archivedate=2019-08-04 |dead-url=no }}</ref>|group="注释"}}）则旨在揭示该国动物实验的事实，这种实验对人类福祉的极大重要性以及直接归因于它们的对人类生命和健康的巨大拯救”<ref>{{cite book|title=Publications of the Research Defence Society: March 1908–1909; Selected by the committee|year=1909|publisher=Macmillan|location=London|page=xiv}}</ref>。

在19世纪60年代[[亨利·柏格|亨利·柏格]]成立美国防止虐待动物协会（ASPCA）时，在美国首次出现反对在医学研究中使用动物的声音。之后于1883年在美国成立了第一个专门的反活体解剖组织[[美國愛護動物協會|美國愛護動物協會]]（AAVS）。{{FACT|这个时代的反活体解剖主义者普遍认为，怜悯的传播是文明的伟大事业，并认为活体解剖对被解剖的对象来说是残酷的。|time=2019-08-25}}然而，在美国，抗争主义者的努力在每个立法机构中都被击败，并被医学界的优越组织和影响所压倒。总的来说，这项运动在1966年《实验动物福利法》通过之前几乎没有立法成功的先例<ref>Buettinger, Craig (1 January 1993) [https://web.archive.org/web/20080215121937/http://www.encyclopedia.com/doc/1G1-13506650.html Antivivisection and the charge of zoophil-psychosis in the early twentieth century.] ''The Historian''.</ref>。

==微生物等级分类==

依据体内寄生的[[微生物|微生物]]种类，实验动物按从低到高的标准可分为普通级（{{lang|en|conventional}}，可缩写为CV）、[[无特定病原体动物|无特定病原体级]]（{{lang|en|specific pathogen free}}，可缩写为“SPF”），以及无菌级（{{lang|en|germ free}}，可缩写为GF）{{NoteTag|中国大陆地区会将实验动物的普通级进一步进行划分为基础级和清洁级，其中清洁级动物是根据中国大陆的具体条件而设立的。以上信息来自：{{cite book |author1=秦川 |display-authors=etal |title=实验动物学 |date=2010 |publisher=人民卫生出版社 |location=北京 |isbn=978-7-117-13145-2|pages=22-23}}}}<ref name="Karaman2015">{{cite journal|last1=Karaman|first1=Meral|title=Microbiological Standardization in Small Laboratory Animals and Recommendations for the Monitoring|journal=Journal of Clinical and Analytical Medicine|volume=6|issue=5|year=2015|issn=13090720|doi=10.4328/JCAM.2195}}</ref>。普通级的实验动物的饲养环境无任何防护措施。无特定病原体级的实验动物是受国际认可的标准动物模型。这类实验动物饲养在达到一定条件的动物房中，饲养环境能阻止特定病原体在这类实验动物中寄生，以减少对实验结果的影响。而无菌级的实验小鼠需要生活在无菌环境中，体内不含有任何微生物<ref name=Qin2010>{{cite book |author1=秦川 |display-authors=etal |title=实验动物学 |date=2010 |publisher=人民卫生出版社 |location=北京 |isbn=978-7-117-13145-2 |pages=38-42}}</ref>{{rp|22-23}}<ref name="Karaman2015">{{cite journal|last1=Karaman|first1=Meral|title=Microbiological Standardization in Small Laboratory Animals and Recommendations for the Monitoring|journal=Journal of Clinical and Analytical Medicine|volume=6|issue=5|year=2015|issn=13090720|doi=10.4328/JCAM.2195}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |editor=Jann Hau, Gerald L. Van Hoosier, Jr. |title=Handbook of Laboratory Animal Science |date=2003 |publisher=CRC Press |location=Florida |isbn=0-8493-1086-5 |edition=2nd|section=CHAPTER 13: Impact of the Biotic and Abiotic Environment on Animal Experiments}}</ref>。

