准确的全球动物试验数据很难获得；据估计，每年有约1亿只脊椎动物在世界各地进行实验<ref>{{cite journal |last=Taylor |first=Katy |last2=Gordon |first2=Nicky |last3=Langley |first3=Gill |last4=Higgins |first4=Wendy |date=2008 |title=Estimates for worldwide laboratory animal use in 2005 |journal=ATLA |volume=36 |issue=3 |pages=327–42 |pmid=18662096|doi=10.1177/026119290803600310 }}</ref>，欧盟则每年有约1.1千万只脊椎动物被用于实验<ref name="hunter2014">{{cite news | author=Hunter, Robert G. | title=Alternatives to animal testing drive market | quote=While growth has leveled off and there have been significant reductions in some countries, the number of animals used in research globally still totals almost 100 million a year. | work=[[Gen._Eng._Biotechnol._News|Gen. Eng. Biotechnol. News]] | date=2014-01-01 | page=11 | issue=1 | volume=34 | url=http://www.genengnews.com/gen-articles/alternatives-to-animal-testing-drive-market/5095/ | accessdate=2019-08-04 | archive-date=2017-12-01 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201131752/https://www.genengnews.com/gen-articles/alternatives-to-animal-testing-drive-market/5095/ | dead-url=no }}{{open access}}</ref>。而据{{le|纳菲尔德生物伦理委员会|Nuffield Council on Bioethics}}<ref>{{Cite web |title=人类基因组编辑峰会组委会：贺建奎将在争议中如期发言 |url=http://www.bjnews.com.cn/finance/2018/11/26/525123.html |accessdate=2019-08-04 |author=杨砺 |date=2018-11-26 |work=www.bjnews.com.cn |language=zh-cn |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190804080747/http://www.bjnews.com.cn/finance/2018/11/26/525123.html |archivedate=2019-08-04 |quote=……是英国纳菲尔德生物伦理委员会(Nuffield Council on Bioethics)进行…… |dead-url=no }}</ref>报告称，全球年度估计数量为5千万至1亿只。这些数据都不包括虾和果蝇等无脊椎动物<ref name=nuffield45>{{cite web |url=http://www.nuffieldbioethics.org/fileLibrary/pdf/RIA_Report_FINAL-opt.pdf |title=The Ethics of research involving animals |publisher=Nuffield Council on Bioethics |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080625033250/http://www.nuffieldbioethics.org/fileLibrary/pdf/RIA_Report_FINAL-opt.pdf |format=pdf |language=en |archivedate=2008-06-25 |accessdate=2019-08-04 }}</ref>。

[[美国农业部|美国农业部]]联合[[动植物卫生检验署|动植物卫生检验署]]发布了2016年动物研究统计数据。总体而言，美国研究中使用的动物数量（由动物福利法案涵盖）从767,622（2015年）上升6.9％至820,812（2016年）<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://speakingofresearch.com/2017/06/19/usda-publishes-2016-animal-research-statistics-7-rise-in-animal-use/|title=USDA publishes 2016 animal research statistics – 7% rise in animal use|date=2017-06-19|work=Speaking of Research|access-date=2017-12-10|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111191716/https://speakingofresearch.com/2017/06/19/usda-publishes-2016-animal-research-statistics-7-rise-in-animal-use/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。这包括公共和私人机构。通过与统计了所有脊椎动物使用量的欧盟数据进行比较，{{le|研究的发声|Speaking of Research}}估计2016年美国大约有1200万脊椎动物用于研究<ref name="USDA2016">{{cite web|url=http://speakingofresearch.com/facts/statistics/|title=USDA Statistics for Animals Used in Research in the US|publisher=Speaking of Research|date=2008-03-20|accessdate=2019-08-04|archive-date=2014-08-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140806110632/http://speakingofresearch.com/facts/statistics/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2015年发表在《{{le|医学伦理学杂志|Journal of Medical Ethics}}》上的一篇文章认为，近年来美国实验动物的使用量急剧增加。研究人员发现，这种增加主要是由于动物研究中对转基因小鼠的依赖性增加<ref name="GoodmanChandnaRoe" />。

1995年，塔夫茨大学动物和公共政策中心的研究人员估计，1992年美国实验室使用了1.4到2.1千万只动物，远少于1970年所使用的5千万只<ref>Rowan, A., Loew, F., and Weer, J. (1995) "The Animal Research Controversy. Protest, Process and Public Policy: An Analysis of Strategic Issues." ''Tufts University'', North Grafton. cited in Carbone 2004, p. 26.</ref>。1986年，美国国会技术评估办公室报告说，美国使用的动物估计每年从1000万到超过1亿，而他们自己的最佳估计则至少是1700万到2200万<ref>''Alternatives to Animal Use in Research, Testing and Education'', U.S. Congress Office of Technology Assessment, Washington, D.C.:Government Printing Office, 1986, p. 64. In 1966, the Laboratory Animal Breeders Association estimated in testimony before Congress that the number of mice, rats, guinea pigs, hamsters, and rabbits used in 1965 was around 60 million. (Hearings before the Subcommittee on Livestock and Feed Grains, Committee on Agriculture, U.S. House of Representatives, 1966, p. 63.)</ref>。{{FACT|2016年，美国农业部列出的数据包含了60,979只狗、18,898只猫、71,188只非人类灵长类动物、183,237只豚鼠、102,633只仓鼠、139,391只兔子、83,059只农场动物以及161,467只其他哺乳动物，共计820,812只，其中包含除了目标繁殖用小鼠和大鼠之外的所有哺乳动物的统计数据。|time=2019-08-25}}在美国的研究中，狗和猫的使用量分别从1973年的195,157和66,165减少到2016年的60,979和18,898只<ref name="USDA2016" />。

根据英国内政部的数据显示，2017年有379万组动物实验申请<ref name="UK Home Office 2016">{{cite web|date=2017|url=http://www.understandinganimalresearch.org.uk/news/communications-media/animal-research-numbers-in-2017/|title=Animal research numbers in 2017|publisher=Understanding Animal Research|access-date=2019-08-04|archive-date=2020-09-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200917225954/https://www.understandinganimalresearch.org.uk/news/communications-media/animal-research-numbers-in-2017/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。其中2,960组使用非人类灵长类动物，自1988年以来下降了50％以上。这里的动物实验可能是持续数分钟、数月或数年的实验。而大多数动物仅被用于一种实验手法：实验后通常对动物实施安乐死；然而死亡是很多实验以及实验动物的终点<ref name=nuffield45/>。

2017年对英国的动物实验分类为：
* 43％（161万）被评估为亚阈值
* 4％（14万）被评估为无法康复
* 36％（135万）被评为轻度
* 15％（55万）被评为中度
* 4％（14万）被评估为严重<ref name=SR2017>{{cite web |url=https://speakingofresearch.com/facts/uk-statistics/ |title=Home Office Statistics for Animals Used in Research in the UK |publisher=Speaking of Research |date=2012-10-23 |access-date=2019-08-04 |archive-date=2020-11-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125045910/https://speakingofresearch.com/facts/uk-statistics/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>
其中“严重”的实验是指任何以实验对象死亡为实验结束标准或实验预期结果为实验对象死亡的试验，而“中度”的实验则是指例如血液测试或者MRI扫描<ref name="UK Home Office 2016" />
。

===3R===
{{main|3R原则}}
3R原则是指在试验中更加道德地使用动物的指导原则。这些原则最早由{{le|威廉·莫伊·斯特拉顿·罗素|W. M. S. Russell}}{{noteTag|group="译注"|译名参考自《世界人名翻译大辞典》。{{Sfn|新华社译名室|1993|p=2975,1939,2653,2397}}}}和R.L.Burch于1959年首次提出<ref name="altweb.jhsph">Russell, W.M.S. and Burch, R.L., (1959).  ''The Principles of Humane Experimental Technique'', Methuen, London. {{ISBN|0-900767-78-2}} [http://altweb.jhsph.edu/pubs/books/humane_exp/het-toc] {{Wayback|url=http://altweb.jhsph.edu/pubs/books/humane_exp/het-toc |date=20110927060555 }}</ref>。

3R包括：
#减少（Reduction）指的是使研究人员能够从较少的动物获得相当水平的信息，或从相同数量的动物获得更多信息的方法<ref name=Badyal>{{cite journal | authors = Badyal D., Desai C. | year = 2014 | title = Animal use in pharmacology education and research: The changing scenario | url = | journal = Indian Journal of Pharmacology | volume = 46 | issue = 3| pages = 257–265 | doi = 10.4103/0253-7613.132153 | pmid = 24987170 | pmc = 4071700 }}</ref>。
#优化（Refinement）指减轻或减少实验动物潜在痛苦的方法，并增强所用动物的动物福利。这些方法包括非侵入性技术。
#替代（Replacement）是指在可能实现相同的科学目标时，非动物方法优于动物方法的使用。这些方法包括计算机建模<ref name=Badyal/>。
3R的范围比仅仅鼓励动物试验的替代品更广泛，但旨在改善动物福利和科学质量，而无法完全避免在研究中使用动物。3R现已在全球许多研究机构中实施，并已被各种立法和法规采用。<ref name="Ethical">{{cite journal| author1=Liguori, G.| displayauthors=etal| year=2017| title=Ethical Issues in the Use of Animal Models for Tissue Engineering: Reflections on Legal Aspects, Moral Theory, 3Rs Strategies, and Harm-Benefit Analysis| journal=Tissue Engineering Part C: Methods| volume=23| issue=12| pages=850–862| doi=10.1089/ten.TEC.2017.0189| pmid=28756735| url=https://pure.rug.nl/ws/files/51950145/ten.tec.2017.0189.pdf| access-date=2019-08-04| archive-date=2020-09-15| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200915060144/https://pure.rug.nl/ws/files/51950145/ten.tec.2017.0189.pdf| dead-url=no}}</ref>

尽管3R被广泛接受，但许多国家——包括加拿大、澳大利亚、以色列、韩国和德国——报告近年来动物实验使用量的增加，小鼠使用量增加，在某些情况下，鱼类被报告相比于猫、狗、灵长类动物、兔子、豚鼠和仓鼠等有所减少。与其他国家一样，中国也加大了在转基因研究中对动物的使用量，导致动物总体使用量增加。<ref name="GoodmanChandnaRoe">{{cite journal |last1=Goodman |first1=J. |last2=Chandna |first2=A. |last3=Roe |first3=K. |title=Trends in animal use at US research facilities |journal=Journal of Medical Ethics |date=2015 |doi=10.1136/medethics-2014-102404 |pmid=25717142 |url=http://jme.bmj.com/content/early/2015/01/27/medethics-2014-102404.abstract |accessdate=2015-07-07 |volume=41 |issue=7 |pages=567–569 |archive-date=2020-07-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200731035153/https://jme.bmj.com/content/41/7/567.abstract |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Canadian Council on Animal Care |title=2009 CCAC Survey of Animal Use |date=December 2010 |url=http://www.ccac.ca/Documents/Publications/Statistics/Survey_2009.pdf |accessdate=2015-07-07 |journal= |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150607174417/http://www.ccac.ca/Documents/Publications/Statistics/Survey_2009.pdf |archive-date=2015-06-07 |dead-url=yes |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Merkes |first1=M. |last2=Buttrose |first2=R. |title=New code, same suffering: animals in the lab |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2013-08-01/merkes-and-buttrose-animal-testing/4857604 |accessdate=2015-07-07 |agency=The Drum |publisher=ABC |archive-date=2020-11-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129133701/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2013-08-01/merkes-and-buttrose-animal-testing/4857604 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Even |first1=Dan |title=Number of animal experiments up for first time since 2008 |url=http://www.haaretz.com/news/national/number-of-animal-experiments-up-for-firsttime-since-2008.premium-1.526516 |accessdate=2015-07-07 |agency=Haaretz |date=2013-05-29 |archive-date=2021-01-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210119160033/https://www.haaretz.com/.premium-first-rise-in-animal-testing-since-2008-1.5270628 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |title=Rise in animal research in South Korea in 2017 |date=2018-04-20 |url=https://speakingofresearch.com/2018/04/12/rise-in-animal-research-in-south-korea-in-2017/ |accessdate=2017-07-23 |journal= |archive-date=2020-11-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128104805/https://speakingofresearch.com/2018/04/12/rise-in-animal-research-in-south-korea-in-2017/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Number of laboratory animals in Germany |url=http://www.mpg.de/286584/Numbers |website=Max-Planck-Gesellschaft |publisher=Max-Planck-Gesellschaft |accessdate=2015-07-07 |archive-date=2020-09-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200923032519/https://www.mpg.de/animal-studies-portal/animal-research |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Kong |first1=Q. |last2=Qin |first2=C. |title=Analysis of current laboratory animal science policies and administration in China |journal=ILAR |date=2009 |volume=51 |issue=1 |pages=e1–e11  |pmid=20075493 |doi=10.1093/ilar.51.1.e1}}</ref>

===无脊椎动物===

[[Image:Drosophila_melanogaster_-_front_(aka).jpg|thumb]]是一种常用于动物试验的无脊椎动物。]]

{{FACT|尽管在动物试验中使用的无脊椎动物远比脊椎动物多，但这些研究在很大程度上不受法律管制。|time=2019-08-25}}最常用的无脊椎动物物种是[[黑腹果蝇|黑腹果蝇]]和[[秀丽隐杆线虫|秀丽隐杆线虫]]<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Antoshechkin I, Sternberg PW | title = The versatile worm: genetic and genomic resources for Caenorhabditis elegans research | journal = Nature Reviews Genetics | volume = 8 | issue = 7 | pages = 518–32 | year = 2007 | pmid = 17549065 | doi = 10.1038/nrg2105 }}</ref>。这些无脊椎动物在动物试验中较脊椎动物有不少优势，这其中包括生命周期短，以及可以容纳和研究大量数据。以秀丽隐杆线虫为例，[[线虫动物门|这种蠕虫]]的身体是完全透明的，而且科学界也已经完成了对他的[[基因组|基因组]]测序，而对果蝇的研究可以使用到一系列惊人的遗传工具<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Matthews KA, Kaufman TC, Gelbart WM | title = Research resources for Drosophila: the expanding universe | journal = Nature Reviews Genetics | volume = 6 | issue = 3 | pages = 179–93 | year = 2005 | pmid = 15738962 | doi = 10.1038/nrg1554 }}</ref>。然而，由于其相对简单的器官组织以及缺乏适应性免疫系统阻碍了这些蠕虫更深入的被用于如[[免疫系统|疫苗研发]]等的医学研究领域<ref name=Schulenburg>{{cite journal |vauthors=Schulenburg H, Kurz CL, Ewbank JJ | title = Evolution of the innate immune system: the worm perspective | journal = Immunological Reviews | volume = 198 | pages = 36–58 | year = 2004 | pmid = 15199953 | doi = 10.1111/j.0105-2896.2004.0125.x }}</ref>。同样，果蝇免疫系统与人类的免疫系统差异巨大<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Leclerc V, Reichhart JM | title = The immune response of Drosophila melanogaster | journal = Immunological Reviews | volume = 198 | pages = 59–71 | year = 2004 | pmid = 15199954 | doi = 10.1111/j.0105-2896.2004.0130.x }}</ref>，昆虫中的疾病可能与脊椎动物的疾病不同<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Mylonakis E, Aballay A | title = Worms and flies as genetically tractable animal models to study host-pathogen interactions |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_infection-and-immunity_2005-07_73_7/page/3833 | journal = Infection and Immunity | volume = 73 | issue = 7 | pages = 3833–41 | year = 2005 | pmid = 15972468 | pmc = 1168613 | doi = 10.1128/IAI.73.7.3833-3841.2005 }}</ref>；然而，果蝇和[[蜡虫|蜡虫]]都可用于研究以鉴定新的毒力因子或药理活性化合物<ref name="ncbi.nlm.nih.gov">{{cite journal |vauthors=Kavanagh K, Reeves EP | title = Exploiting the potential of insects for in vivo pathogenicity testing of microbial pathogens | journal = FEMS Microbiology Reviews | volume = 28 | issue = 1 | pages = 101–12 | year = 2004 | pmid = 14975532 | doi = 10.1016/j.femsre.2003.09.002 }}</ref><ref name="plosone.org">{{cite journal | vauthors = Antunes LC, Imperi F, Carattoli A, Visca P | title = Deciphering the Multifactorial Nature of Acinetobacter baumannii Pathogenicity | journal = PLoS ONE | volume = 6 | issue = 8 | pages = e22674 | year = 2011 | pmid = 21829642 | pmc = 3148234 | doi = 10.1371/journal.pone.0022674 | editor1-last = Adler | editor1-first = Ben |bibcode = 2011PLoSO...622674A }}</ref><ref name="Aperis G 2011">{{cite journal |vauthors=Aperis G, Fuchs BB, Anderson CA, Warner JE, Calderwood SB, Mylonakis E | title = Galleria mellonella as a model host to study infection by the Francisella tularensis live vaccine strain | journal = Microbes and Infection / Institut Pasteur | volume = 9 | issue = 6 | pages = 729–34 | year = 2007 | pmid = 17400503 | pmc = 1974785 | doi = 10.1016/j.micinf.2007.02.016 }}</ref>。

在早期的研究中，研究人员发现有几种无脊椎动物系统被认为是脊椎动物的可接受替代品<ref>{{Cite journal|vauthors=Waterfield NR, Sanchez-Contreras M, Eleftherianos I, Dowling A, Yang G, Wilkinson P, Parkhill J, Thomson N, Reynolds SE, Bode HB, Dorus S, Ffrench-Constant RH |doi=10.1073/pnas.0711114105|title=Rapid Virulence Annotation (RVA): Identification of virulence factors using a bacterial genome library and multiple invertebrate hosts|year=2008|journal=Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences of the United States of America |volume=105|issue=41|pages=15967–15972 |bibcode = 2008PNAS..10515967W |pmid=18838673 |pmc=2572985}}</ref>。由于昆虫与哺乳动物在先天免疫系统上有一定的相似性，昆虫可以在某些类型的研究中取代哺乳动物。这其中，黑腹果蝇和{{le|大蜡蛾|Galleria mellonella}}对于分析哺乳动物病原体的毒力特性特别重要<ref name="ncbi.nlm.nih.gov"/><ref name="plosone.org"/>。目前科学研究已经证明蜡蛾和其他一些昆虫对于鉴定具有有利生物利用度的药物化合物是十分有价值的<ref name="Aperis G 2011"/>。

===脊椎动物===
{{Further|啮齿类动物实验|德萊茲測試|半數致死量}}
[[File:Chimpanzee_Enos_before_the_flight_of_Mercury-Atlas_5.jpg|thumb]] before insertion into the {{le|水星-宇宙神5号|Mercury-Atlas 5}} capsule in 1961]]
[[Image:Sleep-deprivation-flowerpot-technique-jepoirrier.jpg|thumb]]. The water is within 1 cm of the small flower pot bottom platform where the rat sits. At the onset of sleep, the rat would either fall into the water only to clamber back to the pot to avoid drowning, or its [[nose|nose]] would become submerged into the water [[Acute_stress_reaction|shocking]] it back to an awakened state.]]
在美国，每年使用的大鼠和小鼠的数量估计为1100万<ref name=USDA2016 />到2000万至1亿之间<ref name="Trull">{{cite journal|last1=Trull|first1=F. L.|year=1999|title=More Regulation of Rodents|journal=Science|volume=284|issue=5419|page=1463|bibcode=1999Sci...284.1463T|doi=10.1126/science.284.5419.1463}}</ref>。这其中，由于大小、成本、易于处理和快速繁殖率等方面的优势，小鼠成为最常用的脊椎动物实验物种。其他常用的啮齿动物还有豚鼠、仓鼠和沙鼠等.<ref name=Rosenthal>{{cite journal |vauthors=Rosenthal N, Brown S | title = The mouse ascending: perspectives for human-disease models | journal = Nature Cell Biology | volume = 9 | issue = 9 | pages = 993–9 | year = 2007 | pmid = 17762889 | doi = 10.1038/ncb437 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Mukerjee|first1=M|title=Speaking for the Animals|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_scientific-american_2004-08_291_2/page/96|journal=Scientific American|date=August 2004|volume=291|issue=2|pages=96–97|doi=10.1038/scientificamerican0804-96|bibcode=2004SciAm.291b..96M}}</ref>。小鼠被广泛认为是人类[[遗传性疾病|遗传性疾病]]的最佳模型，其与人类[[基因|基因]]有95%的相似度。随着[[基因工程|基因工程]]技术的出现，可以按需求培育转基因小鼠，并且可以为一系列人类疾病提病理模型<ref name=Rosenthal/>。大鼠也广泛用于生理学、毒理学和癌症研究，但在大鼠身上的遗传操作比小鼠更难，这限制了这种啮齿动物在基础科学中的使用<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Aitman TJ, Critser JK, Cuppen E, Dominiczak A, Fernandez-Suarez XM, Flint J, Gauguier D, Geurts AM, Gould M, Harris PC, Holmdahl R, Hubner N, Izsvák Z, Jacob HJ, Kuramoto T, Kwitek AE, Marrone A, Mashimo T, Moreno C, Mullins J, Mullins L, Olsson T, Pravenec M, Riley L, Saar K, Serikawa T, Shull JD, Szpirer C, Twigger SN, Voigt B, Worley K | title = Progress and prospects in rat genetics: a community view | journal = Nature Genetics | volume = 40 | issue = 5 | pages = 516–22 | year = 2008 | pmid = 18443588 | doi = 10.1038/ng.147 }}</ref>。

2016年，英国的各类实验共使用了超过500,000条鱼和9,000只两栖动物。这其中最多的是斑马鱼和[[非洲爪蟾|非洲爪蟾]]<ref name=UK2017>{{cite web|url=https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/724611/annual-statistics-scientific-procedures-living-animals-2017.pdf|title=Statistics of Scientific Procedures on Living Animals, Great Britain|year=2017|work=UK Home Office|accessdate=2018-07-23|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111232734/https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/724611/annual-statistics-scientific-procedures-living-animals-2017.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2004年，英国有超过20,000只兔子被用于动物试验<ref name=HomeOffice2004>{{cite web|url=http://www.official-documents.gov.uk/document/cm67/6713/6713.pdf|title=Statistics of Scientific Procedures on Living Animals, Great Britain|year=2004|work=British government|accessdate=2012-07-13|archive-date=2007-07-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070702210136/http://www.official-documents.gov.uk/document/cm67/6713/6713.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>。白化兔被广泛用于眼睛刺激性测试（德萊茲測試），因为兔子比其他动物具有更少的泪液分泌，并且白化兔缺乏眼睛色素使得效果更容易可视化。在过去二十年中，用于此目的的兔子数量大幅下降。1996年，英国有3,693例兔眼刺激手术<ref>Statistics of Scientific Procedures on Living Animals, Great Britain, 1996 - UK Home Office, Table 13</ref>，2017年这个数字降为63<ref name=UK2017 />。

====猫====

猫最常用于神经学研究。2016年美国使用了18,898只猫<ref name=USDA2016 />，其中约三分之一用于可能导致“疼痛和/或痛苦”的实验<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aphis.usda.gov/animal_welfare/downloads/reports/Annual-Report-Animal-Usage-by-FY2016.pdf|title=Annual Report Animals|publisher=Aphis.usda.gov|accessdate=2017-08-06|archive-date=2020-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201123182104/https://www.aphis.usda.gov/animal_welfare/downloads/reports/Annual-Report-Animal-Usage-by-FY2016.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>，尽管只有0.1％的猫实验涉及潜在的疼痛，而麻醉药/镇痛药并未缓解这种疼痛。在英国，2017年仅对猫进行了198次手术。在过去十年的大部分时间里，这个数字大约为200次<ref name=UK2017/>。

====犬类====

{{See also|萊卡 (蘇聯太空犬)|苏联太空犬}}
犬被广泛用于生物医学研究、实验探索和教育，特别是[[小猎犬|小猎犬]]，因为它们温和且易于操作。根据{{le|美国人道协会|Humane Society of the United States}}{{noteTag|group="译注"|译名参考自搜狐网<ref>{{Cite web |title=The North Face 和 Timberland 的母公司 VF 宣布不再使用：皮草、安哥拉山羊毛或珍稀动物皮革 |url=http://www.sohu.com/a/139627966_487885 |accessdate=2019-08-10 |author=朱若愚 |date=2017-05-10 |work=www.sohu.com |language=zh-cn |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190810040631/http://www.sohu.com/a/139627966_487885 |archivedate=2019-08-10 |quote=……团和美国人道协会（The Humane Society of the United States）和…… |dead-url=no }}</ref>，部分来源译为“美国人道主义协会”<ref>{{Cite web |title=Prada将从2020年春夏系列起不再使用动物皮草 |url=http://fashion.sina.com.cn/s/fo/2019-05-23/1022/doc-ihvhiews3932606.shtml |accessdate=2019-08-10 |date=2019-05-23 |last=新浪时尚 |work=fashion.sina.com.cn |language=zh-cn |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190810041524/http://fashion.sina.com.cn/s/fo/2019-05-23/1022/doc-ihvhiews3932606.shtml?cre=tianyi&mod=pcpager_china&loc=39&r=9&rfunc=100&tj=none&tr=9 |archivedate=2019-08-10 |quote=……AV）和美国人道主义协会（Humane Society of The United States， HSUS）。…… |dead-url=no }}</ref>}}的说法，它们被用作心脏病学、[[内分泌学|内分泌学]]、骨骼和关节研究中的人类和兽医疾病模型，这些研究往往具有高度侵入性<ref name=HSUSDogs>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080226113001/http://www.hsus.org/animals_in_research/species_used_in_research/dog.html|archivedate=2008-02-26|url=http://www.hsus.org/animals_in_research/species_used_in_research/dog.html|title=Dog profile|publisher=The Humane Society of the United States|language=en|accessdate=2019-08-10|dead-url=no}}</ref>。犬只的最常见用途是在[[國際醫藥法規協和會|國際醫藥法規協和會]]的规定下，排在啮齿类动物试验之后作为第二种物种用于人类或兽医用途新药的安全性评估<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Smith|first1=D|last2=Broadhead|first2=C|last3=Descotes|first3=G|last4=Fosse|first4=R|last5=Hack|first5=R|last6=Krauser|first6=K|last7=Pfister|first7=R|last8=Phillips|first8=B|last9=Rabemampianina|first9=Y|last10=Sanders|first10=J|last11=Sparrow|first11=S|last12=Stephan-Gueldner|first12=M|last13=Jacobsen|first13=SD|date=2002|title=Preclinical Safety Evaluation Using Nonrodent Species: An Industry/ Welfare Project to Minimize Dog Use|journal=ILAR}}</ref>。

美国农业部动物福利报告显示，2016年在美国农业部注册的设施总计使用了60,979只犬只<ref name=USDA2016 />。根据英国内政部的统计，2017年英国有3,847份实验申请使用犬只作为实验对象<ref name=UK2017/>。而在欧盟大量使用犬只的国家中，德国在2016年对犬只进行了3,976次手术实验<ref>{{cite web|url=https://speakingofresearch.com/2018/02/06/germany-sees-7-rise-in-animal-research-procedures-in-2016/|title=Germany sees 7% rise in animal research procedures in 2016|date=2018-02-06|publisher=Speaking of Research|access-date=2019-08-10|archive-date=2020-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201001064202/https://speakingofresearch.com/2018/02/06/germany-sees-7-rise-in-animal-research-procedures-in-2016/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，法国在2016年则进行了4,204次<ref>{{cite web|url=https://speakingofresearch.com/2018/03/20/france-italy-and-the-netherlands-publish-their-2016-statistics/#France|title=France, Italy and the Netherlands publish their 2016 statistics|date=2018-03-20|publisher=Speaking of Research|access-date=2019-08-10|archive-date=2020-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200928211239/https://speakingofresearch.com/2018/03/20/france-italy-and-the-netherlands-publish-their-2016-statistics/#France|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

====非人灵长类====
[[Image:77-cm_primate_cage.jpg|thumb]]

非人类灵长类动物（NHP）常用于毒理学测试、艾滋病及肝炎研究、[[神经学|神经学]]研究、行为和认知、生殖、[[遗传学|遗传学]]和[[异种移植|异种移植]]{{noteTag|group="译注"|译名参考自新浪网<ref>{{Cite web |title=猪心脏在狒狒体内跳动195天，距人体试验仅一步之遥 |url=https://tech.sina.com.cn/d/f/2018-12-07/doc-ihmutuec6962064.shtml |accessdate=2019-08-10 |author=新浪科技综合 |date=2018-12-07 |work=tech.sina.com.cn |language=zh-cn |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20190810061716/https://tech.sina.com.cn/d/f/2018-12-07/doc-ihmutuec6962064.shtml |archivedate=2019-08-10 |dead-url=no }}</ref>}}等领域。他们通常来自野外捕获或是人工繁殖。在美国和中国，大多数灵长类动物是由本国进行人工繁殖，而在欧洲，大多数灵长类动物依靠进口<ref>{{Cite web |title=Read "International Perspectives: The Future of Nonhuman Primate Resources: Proceedings of the Workshop Held April 17-19, 2002" at NAP.edu |url=https://www.nap.edu/read/10774/chapter/1 |accessdate=2019-08-10 |work=Proceedings of the Workshop Held |publisher=NAP.edu |pages=36–45, 46–48, 63–69, 197–200 |language=en |archive-date=2020-09-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200917225830/https://www.nap.edu/read/10774/chapter/1 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[欧盟委员会|欧盟委员会]]报告称，2011年，欧洲各地的实验室总共对6,012只猴子进行了试验<ref>{{cite journal|title=Seventh Report on the Statistics on the Number of Animals used for Experimental and other Scientific Purposes in the Member States of the European Union|journal=Report from the Commission to the Council and the European Parliament|date=2013-05-12|url=http://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/PDF/?uri=CELEX:52013DC0859&from=EN|accessdate=2015-07-09|archive-date=2020-09-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200908213454/https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/PDF/?uri=CELEX:52013DC0859&from=EN|dead-url=no}}</ref>。根据美国农业部的数据，2016年美国有71,188只猴子被用于实验室研究<ref name=USDA2016 />。2014年，有23,465只猴子被进口到美国，其中929只是在野外捕获的<ref>{{cite web|title=U.S. primate import statistics for 2014|url=http://www.ippl.org/gibbon/2015/01/|website=International Primate Protection League|accessdate=2015-07-09|archive-date=2017-07-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170704090032/https://www.ippl.org/gibbon/2015/01/|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。在实验中最常使用的NHP是[[猕猴|猕猴]]<ref name="Humaneprimate"/>；但也使用了{{le|狨|Marmoset}}、[[蜘蛛猴|蜘蛛猴]]和[[松鼠猴|松鼠猴]]等，而在美国还使用[[狒狒|狒狒]]和黑猩猩。截至2015年，美国实验室约有730只黑猩猩可供科学研究<ref>{{cite news|last1=St. Fleur|first1=Nicholas|title=U.S. Will Call All Chimps ‘Endangered’|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/13/science/chimpanzees-endangered-fish-and-wildlife-service.html|accessdate=2015-07-09|agency=New York Times|date=2015-06-12|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108140931/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/06/13/science/chimpanzees-endangered-fish-and-wildlife-service.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

在2003年的一项调查中，研究人员发现89%的单独栖息的灵长类动物会表现出自我伤害或异常的刻板行为，包括起搏、摇摆、拔毛和撕咬其他个体等<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Lutz|first1=C|last2=Well|first2=A|last3=Novak|first3=M|title=Stereotypic and Self-Injurious Behavior in Rhesus Macaques: A Survey and Retrospective Analysis of Environment and Early Experience|journal=American Journal of Primatology|date=2003|volume=60|issue=1|pages=1–15|doi=10.1002/ajp.10075|pmid=12766938}}<!--|accessdate=9 July 2015--></ref>。

首例转基因灵长类动物随着一项可以将新基因引入[[恒河猴|恒河猴]]基因的技术的发展于2001年诞生<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Chan AW, Chong KY, Martinovich C, Simerly C, Schatten G | title = Transgenic monkeys produced by retroviral gene transfer into mature oocytes | journal = Science | volume = 291 | issue = 5502 | pages = 309–12 | year = 2001 | pmid = 11209082 | doi = 10.1126/science.291.5502.309 | bibcode = 2001Sci...291..309C }}</ref>。这种转基因技术现在正被用于寻找治疗[[遗传病|遗传病]][[亨丁頓舞蹈症|亨廷顿氏病]]的方法<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Yang SH, Cheng PH, Banta H, Piotrowska-Nitsche K, Yang JJ, Cheng EC, Snyder B, Larkin K, Liu J, Orkin J, Fang ZH, Smith Y, Bachevalier J, Zola SM, Li SH, Li XJ, Chan AW | title = Towards a transgenic model of Huntington's disease in a non-human primate | journal = Nature | volume = 453 | issue = 7197 | pages = 921–4 | year = 2008 | pmid = 18488016 | pmc = 2652570 | doi = 10.1038/nature06975 | bibcode = 2008Natur.453..921Y }}</ref>。关于非人类灵长类动物的著名研究已经成为脊髓灰质炎疫苗研发以及[[腦深層刺激手術|腦深層刺激手術]]发展的一部分，而这类研究目前最重的非毒物学用途出现在猴类艾滋病模型[[SIV|SIV]]中<ref name=TheRoyalSociety/><ref name="Humaneprimate">Kathleen M. Conlee, Erika H. Hoffeld and Martin L. Stephens (2004) [https://web.archive.org/web/20080227041442/http://www.worldcongress.net/2002/proceedings/C2%20Conlee.pdf Demographic Analysis of Primate Research in the United States], ''ATLA'' 32, Supplement 1, 315–322</ref><ref name=Emborg/>。然而在2008年，一项禁止欧盟各成员国所有灵长类动物试验的提案引发了激烈的争论<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/science/2008/nov/02/primate-monkey-animal-testing-drugs|title=Ban on primate experiments would be devastating, scientists warn|work=[[The_Observer|The Observer]]|date=2008-11-02|first=Robin|last=McKie|location=London|accessdate=2019-08-11|archive-date=2020-09-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200918022236/https://www.theguardian.com/science/2008/nov/02/primate-monkey-animal-testing-drugs|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===来源===
脊椎动物和无脊椎动物的来源各不相同。大多数实验室使用从几个主要库存中心提供的菌株和突变体来自行繁殖和饲养苍蝇以及其他蠕虫等<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ncrr.nih.gov/comparative_medicine/resource_directory/invertebrates.asp|title=Invertebrate Animal Resources|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071025061451/http://www.ncrr.nih.gov/comparative_medicine/resource_directory/invertebrates.asp|archivedate=2007-10-25|work=National Center for Research Resources|website=ncrr.nih.gov|accessdate=2019-08-12|dead-url=no}}</ref>。对于实验用的脊椎动物，其主要来源包括饲养者和经销商，如提供目的繁殖和野生捕获动物的{{le|Covance|Covance}}和[[查尔斯河实验室|查尔斯河实验室]]；提供野生动物交易的企业如{{le|Nafovanny|Nafovanny}}。部分动物收容所也直接向实​​验室提供实验用动物<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.aesop-project.org/Oversight.htm |title=Who's Who of Federal Oversight of Animal Issues |publisher=Aesop-project.org |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070922123927/http://www.aesop-project.org/Oversight.htm |archivedate=2007-09-22 |accessdate=2019-08-12 }}</ref>。还有大型中心来分发[[转基因动物|转基因动物]]的变种；例如{{le|国际基因剔除小鼠联盟|International Knockout Mouse Consortium}}旨在为小鼠基因组中的每个基因分组提供对应的[[基因剔除小鼠|基因剔除小鼠]]<ref>{{cite journal |vauthors=Collins FS, Rossant J, Wurst W | title = A mouse for all reasons | journal = Cell | volume = 128 | issue = 1 | pages = 9–13 | year = 2007 | pmid = 17218247 | doi = 10.1016/j.cell.2006.12.018 }}</ref>。
[[Image:Muizenkooi_met_houten_muizen_(3).JPG|thumb]]
在美国，[[明尼苏达州|明尼苏达州]]、[[犹他州|犹他州]]、[[俄克拉荷马州|俄克拉荷马州]]和[[爱荷华州|爱荷华州]]这四个州要求由专门的动物庇护所为研究设施提供实验用动物。另外有14个州明确禁止这种做法，而其余的州则默许或没有相关立法管束<ref name=ASPCAdealers>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080627163237/http://www.aspca.org/site/PageServer?pagename=kids_ri_animaltesting_comefrom|archivedate=2008-06-27|title=Animal Testing: Where Do the Animals Come From?|work=ASPCA|url=http://www.aspca.org/site/PageServer?pagename=kids_ri_animaltesting_comefrom|language=en|quote=American Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals. According to the ASPCA, the following states prohibit shelters from providing animals for research: Connecticut, Delaware, Hawaii, Maine, Maryland, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, New Jersey, New York, Pennsylvania, Rhode Island, South Carolina, Vermont, and West Virginia|accessdate=2019-08-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>。美国也允许使用野生捕获的灵长类动物，而在1995年至1999年期间，有1,580只野生狒狒进口到美国。1995年至2000年间进口的灵长类动物中有一半是由查尔斯河实验室或Covance负责的，Covance是美国最大的{{le|国际灵长类动物贸易|International primate trade|灵长类动物进口商}}<ref>{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070708204056/http://www.ippl.org/04-25-07c.html|archivedate=2007-07-08|title=U.S. Primate Imports Spike|url=http://www.ippl.org/04-25-07c.html|work=International Primate Protection League|date=2007-04|language=en|accessdate=2019-08-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>。联邦政府规定实验动物经销商分两类：A级育种者由美国农业部许可出售用于研究目的的动物，而B级经销商则被许可从“随机来源”，例如拍卖、收容所和报纸广告来收购动物。一些B级经销商常被指控绑架宠物和非法捕获流浪动物，这种做法被称为“bunching”<ref name=Gillham/><ref name="Class B dealers">{{cite web|url=http://www.hsus.org/animals_in_research/class_b_dealers/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100429102206/http://www.hsus.org/animals_in_research/class_b_dealers/|archivedate=2010-04-29|publisher=Humane Society of the United States|language=en|title=Pets Used in Experiments : The Humane Society of the United States|accessdate=2019-08-14|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.aesop-project.org/Oversight.htm|title="Who's Who of Federal Oversight of Animal Issues"|archiveurl=ht